    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Aberteifi — Magical Wings activity guide</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260616-aberteifi-activity-guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 10:37:50 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260616-aberteifi-activity-guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Authored by artist Pip Lewis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;magical-wings---creating-layered-artworks-with-artist-piplewis&#34;&gt;Magical Wings - creating layered artworks with artist Pip Lewis&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;outline&#34;&gt;Outline&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#0-overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#1-pattern-sheet&#34;&gt;Pattern sheet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#2-photo-lottery&#34;&gt;Photo lottery&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#3-tracing-outline&#34;&gt;Tracing outline&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#4-adding-patterns&#34;&gt;Adding patterns&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#5-adding-detail&#34;&gt;Adding detail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#6-naming-the-species&#34;&gt;Naming the species&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;0-overview&#34;&gt;0. Overview&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This guide describes the processes involved in creating layered artworks using acetate and paper, drawing and marker art techniques. &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The art process were designed to explore and learn about the range of pattern, line and colour found on the wings of specific Butterflies and Moths species living in Oak Tree  - and the function this has on their survival.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Aberteifi — Project outline</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260615-aberteifi-project-outline/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 16:09:20 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260615-aberteifi-project-outline/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Authored by artist Pip Lewis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The focus of the project in Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi was the biodiversity to be found in an Oak tree.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We chose the Oak tree as the over-arching subject as it acts as a miniature, living ecosystems and as such presents a huge range of opportunities for the ecologist and artist to explore and devise sessions for the pupils.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I facilitated four morning art workshops worked with 23 pupils in Dosbarth Blodeuwedd — dividing the class into two groups of 12, and facilitated two morning sessions in the classroom, with each group.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi Workshop 5 — Moths &amp; Butterflies of the Oak</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260611-aberteifi-workshop-5/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 21:04:14 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260611-aberteifi-workshop-5/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In the final workshop, Group B students added the colour detail of the patterns to the butterfly and moth wings, following on from the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-workshop-4/&#34;&gt;tracing and outlining in workshop 4&lt;/a&gt;. They also added the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-lepidoptera-species/&#34;&gt;Welsh translation of their English names&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The students had an evaluation at the end of the morning, based on three questions:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;How much did you learn?&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;How proud of yourself are you?&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Which part of the artwork did you enjoy the most?&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The students added their response to each question by adding a mark &amp;ndash; the nearer the centre the mark was placed on the target indicated the higher the student rated their achievement /enjoyment or learning relating to the specific questions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Moth &amp; butterfly species and the Oak / Derwen</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-lepidoptera-species/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 20:51:12 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-lepidoptera-species/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;For the &lt;a href=&#34;https://storiwyllt.cymru/posts/260521-aberteifi-workshop-4/&#34;&gt;second set of workshops&lt;/a&gt;, artist Pip Lewis prepared a whole set of colour print outs of moths and butterflies that are associated with the Oak tree. Here is the list of their names in Latin, English and Welsh, plus links to Wikipedia pages.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;butterfly-and-moth-species&#34;&gt;Butterfly and Moth species&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Moth species&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;English name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Welsh name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blotched_emerald&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Comibaena bajularia&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Blotched Emerald&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Emrallt Blotiog&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_arches&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Lymantria monacha&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Black Arches&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Siobyn Bwaog&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carterocephalus_palaemon&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Carterocephalus palaemon&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Chequered Skipper&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Gwibiwr Y Llennyrch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catocala_sponsa&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Catocala sponsa&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Dark Crimson Underwing&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Ôl-adain Ruddgoch Dywyll&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apoda_limacodes&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apoda limacodes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Festoon&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Llusgwyfyn Rhuban&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyploca_ridens&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Polyploca ridens&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Frosted Green&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Tant Siriol&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lackey_moth&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Malacosoma neustria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Lackey&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Gwaswyfyn&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acleris_literana&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Acleris literana&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Lichen Button&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;-&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclophora_punctaria&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cyclophora punctaria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Maiden&amp;rsquo;s Blush&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Moca Gwridog&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Griposia_aprilina&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Griposia aprilina&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Merveille du Jour&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Gwyfyn Cennog&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oak_hook-tip&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Watsonalla binaria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Oak Hook-tip&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Bachadain Y Deri&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cymatophorina&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cymatophorina diluta&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Oak Lutestring&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Tant Y Deri&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biston_strataria&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Biston strataria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Oak Beauty&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Rhisglyn Y Derw&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oak_eggar&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Lasiocampa quercus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Oak Eggar&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Wylun Deri&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scalloped_oak&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Crocallis elinguaria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Scalloped Oak&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Carpiog Y Derw&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plagodis_dolabraria&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Plagodis dolabraria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Scorched Wing&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Adain Ddeifiog&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Butterfly species&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;English name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Welsh name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apatura_iris&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apatura iris&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Purple Emperor&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Mantell Borffor&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speckled_wood_(butterfly)&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pararge aegeria&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Speckled Wood&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Gweirlöyn Brych&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi Workshop 4 — Moths &amp; Butterflies of the Oak</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-workshop-4/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 20:04:13 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260521-aberteifi-workshop-4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Guest post by artist Pip Lewis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;group-b--butterflies--moths&#34;&gt;Group B &amp;ndash; Butterflies &amp;amp; Moths!&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;patterns-in-nature---introduction&#34;&gt;Patterns in Nature - Introduction &lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Pip introduced the theme of Butterflies and Moths living in oak Trees and the patterns and shapes they have on their wings and showed an example of the layered artworks of butterflies and moths that live and forage in Oak Trees which the pupils will be making.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The art process involved in making the final image will include tracing, working with colour, black and white and marker pens,  patterns shapes and letter stencils as well as incorporating design and layout skills for the final text.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi — Oak leaf collages</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260519-aberteifi-leaf-collage/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 15:37:43 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260519-aberteifi-leaf-collage/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Inspired by artist Pip Lewis‘s most excellent &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/260507-aberteifi-workshop-3/&#34;&gt;collage exercise with the bird artwork&lt;/a&gt; the previous week with Group A, teacher Mari Roberts created collages of Oak leaves with Group B based on observational drawings the children had made.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent example of how techniques, skills and knowledge can be transferred across different groups within the school.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;oriel-gallery&#34;&gt;Oriel Gallery&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;gallery caption-position-bottom caption-effect-slide hover-effect-zoom hover-transition&#34; itemscope itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ImageGallery&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#x9;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;link rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; href=http://localhost:1313/css/hugo-easy-gallery.css /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;box&#34; &gt;&#xA;    &lt;figure  itemprop=&#34;associatedMedia&#34; itemscope itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ImageObject&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;img&#34; style=&#34;background-image: url(&#39;https://res.cloudinary.com/naturceredigion/image/upload/v1781880244/260519-aberteifi-leaf-collage-dark-veins-up.jpg&#39;);&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img itemprop=&#34;thumbnail&#34; src=&#34;https://res.cloudinary.com/naturceredigion/image/upload/v1781880244/260519-aberteifi-leaf-collage-dark-veins-up.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Thin dark veined Oak leaf collage&#34;/&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;a href=&#34;https://res.cloudinary.com/naturceredigion/image/upload/v1781880244/260519-aberteifi-leaf-collage-dark-veins-up.jpg&#34; itemprop=&#34;contentUrl&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;        &lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;            &lt;p&gt;Thin dark veined Oak leaf collage&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi Workshop 3 — Birds of the Oak</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260507-aberteifi-workshop-3/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 16:30:47 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260507-aberteifi-workshop-3/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Guest post by project artist Pip Lewis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;adar-y-dderw-birds-of-the-oak&#34;&gt;Adar y Dderw &amp;ndash; birds of the Oak&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Pip continued working with Group A, creating layered artworks made with acetate . The process involves overlaying drawing and collage, and adding text, and will be exhibited in the Stori Wyllt Gathering in Stiwdio 3 in Aberteifi on Monday 29th June.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Prior to the workshop Pip selected and printed A3 photos of different birds who live and forage in oak trees. The students drew lots last week to find out which bird they would be focusing on in their final artwork. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
