    <item>
      <title>List of bird species and the Oak / Derwen</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260507-aberteifi-bird-species-list/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 09:54:20 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260507-aberteifi-bird-species-list/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is the list of bird species that have relationship with the Oak / Derwen, that the artist Pip Lewis is working on with the Group A students.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Species&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;English name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Welsh name&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_redstart&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Phoenicurus phoenicurus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Redstart&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Tingoch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_pied_flycatcher&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ficedula hypoleuca&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Pied Flycatcher&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Gwybedog Brith&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rook_(bird)&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Corvus frugilegus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Rook&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Ydfan&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_tit&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Parus major&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Great Tit&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Titw Mawr&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurasian_blue_tit&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cyanistes caeruleus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Blue Tit&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Titw Tomos Las&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurasian_blue_tit&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Anthus trivialis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Tree Pipit&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Corhedydd Y Coed&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wood_warbler&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Phylloscopus sibilatrix&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Wood Warbler&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Telor Y Coed&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_wood_pigeon&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Columba palumbus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Wood Pigeon&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Colomen Y Goedwig&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_starling&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sturnus vulgaris&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Starling&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Drudwy&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_owl&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Athene noctua&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Little Owl&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Tylluan Fach&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurasian_jay&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Garrulus glandarius&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Jay&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Sgrech Y Coed&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_robin&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Erithacus rubecula&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Robin&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Robin Goch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_spotted_woodpecker&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dendrocopos major&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Great Spotted Woodpecker&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Cnocell Fraith Fwyaf&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawfinch&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Coccothraustes coccothraustes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Hawfinch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Gylfrinbraff&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurasian_nuthatch&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sitta europaea&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Nuthatch&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Delor Y Cnau&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://res.cloudinary.com/naturceredigion/image/upload/v1778770101/260507-aberteifi-workshop3-acetate-robin.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Collage of Robin Goch&#34;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Collage of Robin Goch, work-in-progress&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi Workshop 2 — Shape of the Oak leaf</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260430-aberteifi-workshop-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:29:17 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260430-aberteifi-workshop-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The class was split into two groups (Group A &amp;amp; Group B ) and Pip worked with Group A, with the students initially studying Oak leaves and making observational drawings drawing of them with pencils, identifying the midrib tip, shape and margins of the leaf. The students also  worked with white charcoal pencils drawings of Oak leaves on black paper, and black charcoal pencils on white paper, and graphite sticks to create rubbings of the leaves.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi Workshop 1 — ID around the Oak</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260417-aberteifi-workshop-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 13:09:19 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260417-aberteifi-workshop-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Underlining the variation in the different schools, settings and people across Stori Wyllt, we didn’t have an ecologist for Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi for the first two workshops, as Yusef Samari has a &lt;em&gt;very&lt;/em&gt; full calendar with the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wwbic.org.uk/projects/your-wild-patch-eich-darn-gwyllt/&#34;&gt;Your Wild Patch / Eich Darn Gwyllt&lt;/a&gt; project.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This meant I was leading the first session, very ably aided by teacher Mari Roberts (who has a Zoology degree!) I gave a very brief introduction to ecoystems, and talked a bit about the wildlife benefits of the Oak, and the amazing array and number of species it supports. And then out to the seating area under a pair of Oak trees, beyond the playground and playing field, newly garlanded with a shining green fence.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi and wildlife partnership work in Cardigan</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/260401-aberteifi-recap/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 17:30:15 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/260401-aberteifi-recap/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The Grassland ID workshops, organised by &lt;a href=&#34;https://naturceredigion.cymru&#34;&gt;Ceredigion Nature Partnership&lt;/a&gt; in 2025 were a great success, and showed a fantastic working partnership between the &lt;a href=&#34;https://ygaberteifi.co.uk/&#34;&gt;Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/groups/842965730705207/&#34;&gt;Friends of Netpool Park&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wwbic.org.uk/&#34;&gt;West Wales Biodiversity Information Centre&lt;/a&gt; and the Partnership.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What has inspired &lt;a href=&#34;https://storiwyllt.cymru/&#34;&gt;Stori Wyllt&lt;/a&gt; in addition to the great work at Netpool Park has been the collaboration between the school, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wwha.co.uk/&#34;&gt;Wales &amp;amp; West Housing Assocation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://cardished.cymru/&#34;&gt;Cardished&lt;/a&gt; to create wildlife habitat with residents and students. WWHA received a &lt;a href=&#34;https://naturceredigion.cymru/en/funding/small-grant-scheme/&#34;&gt;Small Grant&lt;/a&gt; from the Partnership for wildlife enhancements across their Ceredigion properties, and this included the creation of bug hotels with the students from Ysgol Gynradd Aberteifi and the residents of &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/525723799&#34;&gt;Llys Owen&lt;/a&gt;, with a workshop run by Harry from Cardished.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
